[1] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Sat 11 Apr 2009
Fonte: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/pais/cidades/mat/2009/04/11/na-bahia-dengue-ja-fez-40-mil-vitimas-com-32-mortes-755235125.asp>


The number of people who have had dengue in Bahia this year [2009]
has reached 40 000 with 32 deaths. Most fatal victims were children.
Changes in weather, with rain and heat, have caused an increase in
breeding of the transmitter mosquito, _Aedes aegypti_. The main
obstacle in the fight against the disease may be inside the houses
[where the mosquito breeds].

In Itabuna, one of the hardest hit cities in the south of the state,
6900 cases of the disease and 8 deaths were recorded. Doctors and
nurses of the Armed Forces are reinforcing care of the population. In
addition to 3 hydration centers, 2 health units with 70 beds were
opened.

In Salvador, the increase in the number of cases is of concern in the
health area. The city has faced a lot of rain and then hot weather,
and these conditions favor the proliferation of the mosquito. In the
capital, there have been 352 confirmed cases of dengue and more than
1700 reported [cases].

The fight against breeding of the mosquito that transmits dengue has
also been intensified in areas with the highest levels of
infestation. Despite all the warnings and all the recommendations of
health authorities, 40 percent of breeding sites in Salvador are
found in barrels and open tanks and in vases and dishes of plants.

--
