[2] Brazil (Mato Grosso)
Date: Sun 12 Apr 2009
Source: O Globo [edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/sp/mat/2009/04/12/morre-quarta-vitima-de-dengue-hemorragica-em-cuiaba-755238920.asp>


A man of 56 years died, a victim of DHF. The case was confirmed by
the state Secretariat of Health. Partial data show that from January
2009 until this Saturday [11 Apr 2009], the state of Mato Grosso has
now reported 5180 cases of dengue, 314 [of them] serious. Of these,
180 were in Varzea Grande and 100 in Cuiaba. Besides those 2 cities,
severe cases of dengue occurred in the municipalities of Nova
Olimpia, Nova Mutum, Pocone, Canarana, Tangara da Serra, Nobres,
Rosario Oeste and Caceres, among others.

--
