[4] Saudi Arabia
Date: Mon 13 Apr 2009
Source: Saudi Gazette [edited]
<http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2009041334934>


[There have been] 2 dengue fever deaths at the King Faisal Hospital
in Makkah. Authorities have become increasingly concerned at an
apparent rise in the cases of dengue fever, with the National Society
for Human Rights noting last week some 139 cases receiving treatment
at a Makkah hospital in the last 3 months alone. The Minister of
Agriculture made a tour of sites in Jeddah last week to oversee
efforts to combat the virus.

[Byline: Hatim Al-Masoudi]

