[8] Society Islands (Tahiti)
Date: Sat 11 Apr 2009
Source: La Depeche [in French, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.ladepeche.pf/fenua/social/4274-150-cas-de-dengue-de-type-4.html>


Since the beginning of 2009, through the end of [epidemiological]
week [EW] 14 [30 Mar-5 Apr 2009], 150 cases of dengue 4 were
laboratory confirmed. The cases are located on the islands of Tahaa,
Tahiti, Bora Bora, Raiatea, Moorea and Ua-Pou. For [EW] 14 (30 Mar to
5 Apr 2009), 44 new confirmed cases of dengue were registered in the
Bureau for Public Health Surveillance, including 27 cases of dengue
[virus type] 4, 3 cases of dengue [virus type] 1 and 14 cases not
serotyped to date. As of yet, no severe form [of dengue; DHF] has
been reported. Among the 27 new confirmed cases of dengue 4, 11 were
residents of Tahiti, 4 of Bora Bora, 4 of Tahaa, 4 of Raiatea, 2 of
Ua-Pou and one of Moorea. Half of confirmed cases of dengue [virus
type] 4 [infection] are aged 5-19 years (46 percent) and 2 cases less
than 5 years.

As of 8 Apr [2009], at the beginning of EW 15, 7 new cases of dengue
have been laboratory confirmed, of which one was dengue [virus
serotype] 4. The weekly number of confirmed dengue cases remains
stable in Bora Bora, Tahaa, Ua-Pou and Raiatea and Tahiti. A new case
was confirmed in Moorea, although no cases had been confirmed after
EW 11 previously.

--
